The paper deals with the verification of anonymity and unlinkability in cryptographic protocols, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of the applied pi calculus and ProVerif tool suggests a focus on formal methods and logic (cs.LO), while the mention of cryptographic primitives and protocols suggests a focus on programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses attacks on privacy properties, which could fall under the category of cybercrime (cs.CY).
